The paper discusses a secure and private approach to multi-party machine learning, which involves the use of cryptographic primitives and blockchain technology. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a fully decentralized peer-to-peer approach, which could fall under the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper also discusses the scalability and fault tolerance of the proposed approach, which could be relevant to the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
